    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-10-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-10-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="86"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d86">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 611.3731/40.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-10-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 25, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1150.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my dispatch No. 1134 of the 18th
                    instant, I have the honor to transmit a copy and translation of a note received
                    this morning from the Cuban Secretary of State.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John B. Jackson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure—Translation.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Cuban Secretary of State</gloss> to
                            the <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-10-25">
                                <hi rend="italic">October 25, 1911</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Minister</hi>: In continuation of the conversation
                        that I had the honor to have with your excellency a few days ago, I beg that
                        you will inquire of your Government if it considers it convenient and
                        immediately feasible to agree with that of Cuba upon the extension for
                        another five years of the treaty of commercial reciprocity that is still in
                        force, though automatically; and if it would be willing to enter into
                        negotiations with a view to the modfication of the treaty in the sense of
                        providing for greater advantages for some American products and for our
                        sugars and tobacco.</p>
                    <p>I avail, etc.,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Manuel Sanguily.</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
